modules.description: Provides functions for scheduling read and write operations on file descriptors with manual buffer management. Works with file descriptors and byte buffers to enable low-level I/O control. Used in scenarios requiring precise timing of I/O operations or reduced overhead compared to higher-level abstractions.

Provides functions to retrieve peer certificates, check session reuse, and obtain PEM-formatted certificate chains from SSL connections. Works with SSL connection objects and handles TLS negotiation for server and client upgrades, applying user-defined handlers after successful encryption. Enables secure communication by managing certificate verification, cipher suites, and SSL version settings.
